fields.ans:
Every fan has his opinion on this topic but during these last 10 years, it has been solely focused on 2 players: Messi and Cristiano. (not considering the future aspects like Neymar). Also,my answer is solely on men’s football.

For me, the best world footballer is no different than other usual players as it is a team sport and these best players provide edge to a team in front of their opponents. Not necessarily they will score at the end, maybe they will pass a ball which was very important for winning the match. Maybe they will help their team to stay motivated till the last whistle or maybe they will tackle like their life depends on it. So, If anyone has been very important to winning all the titles for a team is that best player.

A best player in the world is someone who can do anything with his feet despite of his body constraints, one who is naturally talented and can see what others can’t on the pitch of football.

Lionel Andres Messi Cuccittini “Leo” is by far the greatest footballer on the planet.

Yesterday's match

( IND vs NZ, 3rd ODI, Kanpur)

( There was a list displayed by scorers showing that Virat Kohli became the fastest Batsman to cross 9000 runs in 194 innings followed by ABD( 205) , S. Ganguly ( 228) etc. )

( in the commentary box )

Deep Dasgupta: so, Viru, why are not you in the list?

Virender Sehwag: (after gloryfying himself a bit) because I always believed in bettering my strike rate, rather than average ( and blah blah ! )

VVS & DD Gupta : but still ?

Virender Sehwaag: “scorers chahte to mera naam bhi is list mein daal date, thodi hera-pheri hi to karni thi, main bhi top par aa jaata”

( if the scorers would want my name would have also featured in the list making me appear in the top )

Now take a look..

Virender Sehwag's ODI stats

As much as I hate to admit it, because I'm a Real Madrid fan, it's true. Lionel Messi is the best player right now and he's the best player ever when we look at the numbers. But football is not just numbers is it? For me, it's the joy that brings​ to the people who love the game which matters the most. I'm not saying that Messi doesn't make me feel that way. He's a magician with the ball at his feet. So is Cristiano at his best. But the absolute bloody best-ever? I doubt it. Because I've seen this man in action.
